        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Razor sharp coral growths erupt from the ground, transforming the landscape into a dangerous coral reef. You can create a third nonoverlapping burst if the centers of all three bursts are underwater. Creatures in the area when the spell is cast take 6d6 piercing damage and must attempt a basic Reflex save. A creature that critically fails its saving throw also takes [[/r 1d6[bleed]]]. The area becomes difficult terrain and hazardous terrain. A creature that moves through the area takes [[/r 3[piercing]]] damage for every square of that area it moves into.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The initial piercing damage increases by 3d6, and the hazardous terrain damage increases by [[/r 1[piercing]]].</p>"
